() N
(    This is a server-client process for DECstation 5000/200) N
(    As a server it waits for a connection on a socket given) N
(    as an argument; when the connection has been settled,) N
(    the following informations must be read through the) N
(    communication channel:) N
() N
(    - machine and socket for alarm messages, mode) N
(      \( "NONE anything else" means 'no alarm' \)) N
(      \( mode=0 means 'stub mode' ; mode=1 means 'normal mode' \)) N
(    - other datas, server-dependent.) N
() N
(    Depending on the first bunch of informations read,) N
(    alarm are managed or not.) N
(    In both cases the server enter an infinite loop,) N
(    waiting for commands and requests from client.) N
(    When alarm are managed the server enable periodic checks) N
(    triggered by alarm\(\) system call.) N
() N
(    usage: server_name socket) N
(           0   1) N
() N
(    example: ma_server 2001) N
() N
(    this server uses the RS232 tty driver, and the tty which is used) N
(    must be off and set to 9600 baud \(see /etc/inittab: ) N
(        off:/etc/getty  scc3 9600 # used for 147) N
(        off:/etc/getty tty11 9600 # used for 332XT \)) N
() N
(    specific server data: verbose/not-verbose option, tty name) N
(                          [-v/-n]                     /dev/tty[11-18]) N
() N
(***********************************************************************/) N
